test players in World Rugby.\", \"from\": 843, \"to\": 904, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 892, \"end\": 903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Rugby\", \"score\": 0.9999999999258762, \"rank\": 7.420166895298569e-11, \"text\": \"World Rugby\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Rugby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Rugby\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Therefore, it is clear that speed runs in the family (pun-intended).\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 973, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As mentioned, van Niekerk famously won Gold in 2016 when he won the 400m.\", \"from\": 975, \"to\": 1048, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, he will not be competing in this year's 400m race as he is solely focused on the 200m race.\", \"from\": 1049, \"to\": 1149, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Additionally, he could represent South Africa in the x100m relay.\", \"from\": 1151, \"to\": 1216, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1184, \"end\": 1196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9797521448398887, \"rank\": 0.020647958704888836, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, he is now listed to only compete in the men's\\u00a0200m,Olympics.comconfirmed.\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1300, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, he is one of the men who could run the 4x100m relay forTeam SA.\", \"from\": 1302, \"to\": 1376, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1373, \"end\": 1375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.724097284717248e-19, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Van Niekerk is also listed in the pool of runners available for sele